H0.text: What general name is given to a rotating star which emits a regular beat of radiation. Rotator

H1.text: What general name is given to a rotating star which emits a regular beat of radiation. Stellar Oscillator

H2.text: What general name is given to a rotating star which emits a regular beat of radiation. Celestial Beacon

H3.text: What general name is given to a rotating star which emits a regular beat of radiation. PULSAR

A4.text: A pulsar is a highly magnetized rotating neutron star that emits beams of electromagnetic radiation out of its magnetic poles.

A5.text: This produces a very precise interval between pulses that ranges from milliseconds to seconds for an individual pulsar.
